Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @garlic{3%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the @British chicken breasts{2} into a #bowl{} with a drizzle of oil and
half the garlic. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix together.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay the chicken into the pan and cook until browned, ~{3-5%minutes} each side.

Meanwhile, trim and halve the @green beans{80}. Cut the @medium tomato{1} into 1cm
pieces. Drain and rinse the @butter beans{1} in a #sieve{}.

Once browned, transfer the chicken to a #baking tray{} and roast on the top shelf
of your oven until cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, boil a half-full #kettle{} for the green beans.

Wipe out the (now empty) frying pan and pop it back onto medium heat with a
drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the @tomato puree{30}(ml) and remaining garlic. Stir-fry for
~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @sugar{1/2}(tsp) and @water for the sauce{200}(ml), @chicken stock paste{10}(g) and
butter beans. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water from your kettle into a #saucepan{} with
@salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Bring back to the boil, then add the green beans and cook until just tender,
~{4-6%minutes}. Drain in a #colander{}.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the tomato chunks, cooked green beans and
half the @fresh pesto{32}. Remove from the heat, then taste and season with
salt and pepper if needed.

Once the chicken is cooked, add it to the cassoulet sauce and turn to coat well.

Spoon the chicken and butter bean cassoulet into your serving dishes.

Drizzle over the remaining pesto.

> TIP: Loosen it with a little oil or water to make it easier to drizzle.

Serve the @wild rocket{20} on the side drizzled with a little oil and seasoned
with salt and pepper.

Enjoy!